// Application Configuration
// Loads server configuration from environment variables with sensible defaults.
// Validates the PORT value on startup and exposes a typed config object.

PROJECT_ROOT is computed relative to this file's location, going one level up
from src/ to the project root. Works in both Bun (import.meta.dir) and Node.js
(import.meta.url) environments.

FUNCTION validatePort() -> number
  Read the PORT environment variable; default to "3737" if absent.
  Parse as integer. Throw if the value is not a number.
  Throw if the value is outside the valid range (1–65535).
  Return the valid port number.

---

config object (exported)                                                   EXPORT
  PORT              - validated port number from validatePort()
  HOST              - from HOST env var, defaults to "0.0.0.0"
  PUBLIC_DIR        - {PROJECT_ROOT}/public
  MAX_FILE_SIZE     - 1048576 (1 MB)
  THUMBNAIL_CACHE_SIZE - 100
  UNDO_HISTORY_SIZE - 50
  WS_RECONNECT_MAX_DELAY - 30000 ms
  UI_DIST_DIR       - {PROJECT_ROOT}/ui/dist
